Step 1:
  Attached the EKS_Role created for K8 Host to Jenkins server

Step 2:
  Install & configure Helm on Jenkins server so that it can deploy on Kubernetes cluster. (Detailed Steps in Software Installation Repo)

Step 3:
  Configure .kube/config file for jenkins in location /var/lib/jenkins/.kube/config and change ownership to Jenkins and change to jenkins user to use the Helm cmd

Step 4: 
  Deploy Sample Application on EKS Kubernetes cluster with Helm (Testing Purpose)
    


 
